SIMPLE: loam
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loam
<hw>Loam</hw> <pr>(l⟦omac⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>l⟦amac⟧m</ets>; akin to D. <ets>leem</ets>, G. <ets>lehm</ets>, and
E. <ets>lime</ets>. See 4th <er>Lime</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
kind of soil; an earthy mixture of clay and sand, with organic matter to
which its fertility is chiefly due.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We wash a wall of <qex>loam</qex>; we labor in vain.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>A mixture of sand, clay, and
other materials, used in making molds for large castings, often without
a pattern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Loam mold</b></col> <fld>(Founding)</fld>, <cd>a mold
made with loam. See <er>Loam</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2.</cd> --
<col><b>Loam molding</b></col>, <cd>the process or business of making
loam molds.</cd> <col><b>Loam plate</b></col>, <cd>an iron plate upon
which a section of a loam mold rests, or from which it is
suspended.</cd> -- <col><b>Loam work</b></col>, <cd>loam molding or loam
molds.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loam</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Loam
<hw>Loam</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Loamed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Loaming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cover, smear, or fill with
loam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>loamless</ent>⟦br⟧
